Key CSS Text and Font Properties
font-family: Defines the typeface of the text. You can specify multiple fonts as a "fallback stack" in case a specific font is unavailable on the userâ€™s system.

Example: font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
font-size: Sets the size of the text. You can use values in pixels (px), ems (em), rems (rem), or percentages.

Example: font-size: 18px;
font-weight: Controls the thickness or "weight" of the font, like normal, bold, lighter, or numeric values from 100 to 900.

Example: font-weight: bold;
text-align: Aligns the text within its containing element, such as left, center, right, or justify.

Example: text-align: center;
color: Sets the color of the text using color names, hex values, RGB, or other CSS color formats.

Example: color: #333333;
Example HTML Document with Styled Text and Fonts

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Text and Font Styling Example</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Main Heading</h1>
    <h2>Subheading</h2>

    <p>This is a paragraph styled with a specific font size, weight, and color. CSS makes it easy to control the look and feel of text on the web.</p>

    <a href="#" class="link">This is a styled link</a>

</body>
</html>
CSS Stylesheet (styles.css)
/* Styles for the main heading */
h1 {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 36px;
    font-weight: bold;
    text-align: center;
    color: darkblue;
}

/* Styles for the subheading */
h2 {
    font-family: Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: normal;
    text-align: left;
    color: #666;
}

/* Styles for the paragraph */
p {
    font-family: 'Verdana', sans-serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: normal;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #333333;
    text-align: justify;
}

/* Styles for the link */
.link {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: bold;
    color: #4CAF50;
    text-decoration: none;
}

.link:hover {
    color: #388E3C;
    text-decoration: underline;
}
